article.description: Dominic Seals had a double-double and Kierra Mallard scored a team-high 15 points to lead Texas Tech past Texas A&M (No. 8 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) 60-53 Wednesday night.
article.headline: Texas Tech gets out in front early, pulls upset
article.linkText: Seals helps Texas Tech stun No. 8 Texas A&M
article.story:
LUBBOCK, Texas --Dominic Seals had a double-double and Kierra Mallard scored a team-high 15 points to lead Texas Tech past Texas A&M (No. 8 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) 60-53 Wednesday night.

Seals had 11 points and 12 rebounds for the Lady Raiders (14-9, 4-5 Big 12). Jordan Murphree and Tilmila Martin each had 12 points for Texas Tech and Maria Moore added 10.

Takia Starks led Texas A&M (18-5, 6-4) with 20 points and Danielle Gant added 12.

Texas Tech used an 8-2 run midway through the first half to take a 14-8 lead and never relinquished the lead.

The Lady Raiders led by 10 in the second half.
